# Prod rebuild workflow

After implementing changes, run the matching command from the **repo root**. Use [scripts/prod-reset-rebuild-backend.sh](scripts/prod-reset-rebuild-backend.sh).

## Cost basis / AVCO / normalization (backend)

Run after any change that affects cost basis, move basis, AVCO replay, classification, clarification, linking, pricing, ingestion normalization, or accounting replay.

Typical paths: `backend/**/costbasis/**`, `backend/**/accounting/**`, `backend/**/pricing/**`, `backend/**/ingestion/**` (normalization, clarification, pipeline).

```bash
./scripts/prod-reset-rebuild-backend.sh --skip-frontend
```

When pricing cache must be cleared (pricing policy or provider changes):

```bash
./scripts/prod-reset-rebuild-backend.sh --clear-pricing-cache --skip-frontend
```

`--skip-frontend` leaves the running `frontend-prod` container untouched.

## Frontend (Angular)

Run after changes under `frontend/**`:

```bash
./scripts/prod-reset-rebuild-backend.sh --frontend-only
```

Rebuilds only `frontend-prod`; does **not** reset Mongo or rebuild backend.

## Full stack (backend + frontend + renormalization)

Use only when both pipeline logic and UI must be verified together (no flags, or explicit `--start-frontend`):

```bash
./scripts/prod-reset-rebuild-backend.sh
```

## Agent checklist

- [ ] Backend pipeline / accounting change → `--skip-frontend` (add `--clear-pricing-cache` if pricing cache invalid)
- [ ] Frontend-only change → `--frontend-only`
- [ ] Run from repo root; wait for script to finish before reporting verification done
